.TH "lc_create" 9 "lc_create" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lc_create \- prepares to track objects in an active set
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct lru_cache *" lc_create
.BI "(const char *name "  ","
.BI "struct kmem_cache *cache "  ","
.BI "unsigned max_pending_changes "  ","
.BI "unsigned e_count "  ","
.BI "size_t e_size "  ","
.BI "size_t e_off "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "name" 12
descriptive name only used in lc_seq_printf_stats and lc_seq_dump_details
.IP "cache" 12
cache root pointer
.IP "max_pending_changes" 12
maximum changes to accumulate until a transaction is required
.IP "e_count" 12
number of elements allowed to be active simultaneously
.IP "e_size" 12
size of the tracked objects
.IP "e_off" 12
offset to the \fIstruct lc_element\fP member in a tracked object
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns a pointer to a newly initialized struct lru_cache on success,
or NULL on (allocation) failure.
